{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"SourceFuncsRef","kind":"identifier"}]}]},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For idle sources, the prepare and check functions always return ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to indicate that the source is always ready to be processed. The prepare"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"function also returns a timeout value of 0 to ensure that the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"poll()"},{"type":"text","text":" call"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"doesn’t block (since that would be time wasted which could have been spent"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"running the idle function)."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For timeout sources, the prepare and check functions both return "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"if the timeout interval has expired. The prepare function also returns","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"a timeout value to ensure that the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"poll()"},{"text":" call doesn’t block too long","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and miss the next timeout."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For file descriptor sources, the prepare function typically returns ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"since it must wait until ","type":"text"},{"code":"poll()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" has been called before it knows whether"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"any events need to be processed. It sets the returned timeout to -1 to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"indicate that it doesn’t mind how long the ","type":"text"},{"code":"poll()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" call blocks. In the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"check function, it tests the results of the "},{"code":"poll()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" call to see if the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"required condition has been met, and returns "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if so.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef"},{"text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"code":"GSourceFuncs","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol","isActive":true},{"text":" conformance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" only as an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference to an existing "},{"code":"GSourceFuncs","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef"},{"text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSourceFuncs"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"struct","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SourceFuncsRef","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"SourceFuncsRef","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"roleHeading":"Structure","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SourceFuncsRef"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib14SourceFuncsRefV","role":"symbol"},"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSourceFuncs"},{"type":"text","text":" struct contains a table of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"functions used to handle event sources in a generic manner.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/sourcefuncsref"]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol"],"title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships"}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"topicSections":[{"title":"Initializers","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef\/init(_:)-1il83","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef\/init(_:)-5idr3","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef\/init(_:)-891i5","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef\/init(_:)-937im","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef\/init(_:)-9qm49","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef\/init(constPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documen